The Termite driver synthesis tool

http://www.termite2.org

Termite must be build on a Linux system. The build process has been thoroughly tested on Ubuntu and Arch Linux.
A working Haskell install is required. You will need to install ghc version 7.8 or greater and cabal-install version 1.20 or greater using your system's package manager.

To clone the needed git subrepos and setup a cabal sandbox:
    $ ./setup.hs

To build CUDD: 
    $ pushd lib/cudd
    $ cp Makefile.64bit Makefile # or Makefile.32bit if you are on a 32 bit system
    $ make libso
    $ popd

To build Termite:
    $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=`pwd`/lib/cudd/libso
    $ cabal update
    $ cabal install termite --extra-include-dirs=`pwd`/lib/cudd/include --extra-lib-dirs=`pwd`/lib/cudd/libso --bindir=bin

To run:
    $ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=`pwd`/lib/cudd/libso
    $ cd documentation/GPIO
    $ ../../bin/termite-app -i main.tsl -s

